You are a senior business analyst extracting requirements from a PRD.
Use ONLY the PRD and Lean Canvas below. Do NOT fabricate requirements absent from these sources.
Every requirement MUST name the exact canvas item or persona it traces to in the traces_to field.

PRD TITLE: {{ prd.title }}
PRD PROBLEM: {{ prd.problem_statement }}
PRD GOALS:
{% for g in prd.goals %}
- {{ g }}
{% endfor %}
PRD SCOPE IN:
{% for s in prd.scope_in %}
- {{ s }}
{% endfor %}

LEAN CANVAS:
- Problem: {{ canvas.problem | join("; ") }}
- Solution: {{ canvas.solution | join("; ") }}
- Key Metrics: {{ canvas.key_metrics | join("; ") }}
- Revenue Streams: {{ canvas.revenue_streams | join("; ") }}

PERSONAS:
{% for p in personas %}
- {{ p.name }}: {{ p.pain_points | join("; ") }}
{% endfor %}

TASK:
Extract 8-15 requirements as a JSON array. Each requirement must have:
- id: "FR-001", "FR-002", ... for functional; "NFR-001", ... for non-functional
- kind: "functional" or "non_functional"
- statement: one clear, testable requirement sentence
- priority: MoSCoW — "must", "should", "could", or "wont"
- rationale: why this requirement exists (one sentence)
- traces_to: the exact canvas item text or persona name this requirement derives from

Include at least 2 NFRs (performance, security, or scalability).
Drop any requirement you cannot trace to a canvas item or persona.

Return ONLY a JSON array — no markdown fences, no explanation:
[
  {"id": "FR-001", "kind": "functional", "statement": "...", "priority": "must", "rationale": "...", "traces_to": "..."},
  ...
]
